[SetUp "1"]

{ Black's Queen is a target.  Show how White can develop with tempo here. } 1.
Nf3
{ This prepares Bg5 next, forcing the Queen to move.   1.h4?  also prepares  Bg5  , but it's a pawn move, not a piece move, so it should be avoided. }
1... Nc6 2. Bg5 Qf5 3. Bd3
{ Bringing another piece into the game while again hitting the Queen.  No other move should be considered. }
3... Qg4 4. h3
{ A key move!  The Queen is so short on squares, our only focus should be attacking her. }
4... Qxg2 { If  4...Qh5  ,  5.g4  also traps the Queen. } 5. Rh2
{ Not  10.Rg1  , which allows  10...Qxh3  and Black's Queen is escaping.   DO develop with tempo.  Do NOT bring your Queen out early, because she can be trapped.  From Steinitz - Bird, London 1866. }
