{ Show how a lead in development matters even without Queens. } 1. O-O-O
{ Castling both gets the King out of the center and brings the Rook into the game with tempo.   11.Rd1  is less accurate because  Nxc2+  is check. }
1... Ne6 2. Bb5+
{ White only had one piece left to develop, so bringing it out should be your main focus. }
2... Ke7 3. Nd5#
{ Even without Queens, White's enormous lead in time allowed him to execute a mating attack.  From Duras - Jes, Pisek 1912. }
