{ Show the power of controlling the center. } 1. e5
{ Push those pawns! d5 first is also fine. ♘c3 follows all the principles and isn't a mistake, but it doesn't use White's main advantage. }
1... Ng8 2. d5 { If you have a mobile central pawn mass, push them! } 2... Nce7
3. d6 { Don't stop pushing! } 3... Nc6 4. Qd5
{ The tactical section will explore the weakness on  f7  in more detail. There are many good moves for White, but taking advantage of the weak  f7  -square is thematic and best. }
4... Nh6 5. Bxh6
{ In the game Greco - NN, 1620, Black played Rf8. What would happen if he recaptured on  h6  ? }
5... gxh6 6. Qxf7# { Mate, of course! } *

[Event "?"]
