{ Show the power of mobile central pawns. } 1. d5
{ Push those pawns! Either pawn move is fine, but note that  8.Nc3  allows the  8...Nxe4  pawn trick:  9.Nxe4  d5  , and Black regains his pieces and breaks up White's pawn center. We'll see this in more detail in the Tactical section. }
1... Ne7 2. e5 { Push push push! } 2... Ne8 3. d6
{ PUSH!  This is so strong because the Bishop on  c8  is completely locked out, and White has a serious space advantage. }
3... cxd6 4. exd6 Ng6 5. Bg5
{ Don't forget to develop with tempo!  From Albin - Shipley, New York 1894. } *

