{ Do we retreat the Knight ... or do we set-up an epic windmill? } 1. Bb6+
{ Of course. } 1... Ke8 2. Nc7+
{ A windmill is a type of tactic where a pair of pieces check the King over and over again; the King can only shuffle back and forth, while the pieces pick up loads of material. }
2... Kd8 3. Nxa8+ { First we gobble the Rook. } 3... Ke8 4. Nc7+
{ In the game Black resigned here.  Why? } 4... Kd8 5. Nd5+
{ If you wanted to be extremely greedy, you could have picked up the a-pawn with  17.Nxa6+  as well, before continuing the windmill. }
5... Ke8 6. Nxf6+
{ The windmill finishes off with an extra Queen.  Windmills are fun!    From Lee Passmoor vs. Leif E Warstad, 1999 }
