{ f7  , or  f2  from Black's perspective, is the weakest square on the board, as it is only protected by the King.  Numerous combinations start with a sacrifice on this square.  The simplest and most thematic involve Bxf7+ and then a follow-up check to regain the material. }
1. Bxf7+
{ This is the standard example.  The Bishop on  g4  is undefended, and White can win it with a discovered attack. }
1... Kxf7 2. Ng5+ { 2.Ne5??  Nxe5  and the Knight defends the Bishop. } 2...
Ke8 3. Qxg4
{ White has won a pawn and Black can no longer castle.  This motif occurs again and again, so there will be many more examples. }
