{ If we move the Knight to  f6  , it defends the  Bg4  , but a related idea still works. }
1. Bxf7+
{ 1.Ne5!  is also good, because if  1...Bxd1  2.Bxf7#  is mate. We will look at this next. }
1... Kxf7 2. Ne5+
{ By going to  e5  instead of  g5  , the Knight hits the  Bg4  as well. } 2...
Ke8 3. Nxg4 Nxg4 4. Qxg4
{ Just like before, White has won a pawn and Black can no longer castle.  If White ever has a  Bc4  and Black plays Bg4, your first thought should be, 'Does a Bxf7 tactic work?' }
