[Black "Tactical Section - Weakness on f7 4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6
{ This is known as the Philidor defence, where Black defends  e5  with his pawn.  The disadvantage is that he can get quite cramped, and numerous traps exist that exploit Black's awkward development.  Remember, we do NOT want to hinder our development if possible. }
3. d4 Nd7 4. Bc4
{ f7  is the eternal weak point, so developing the Bishop here makes perfect sense. }
4... Be7
{ Black's position is so cramped that this natural move is actually a big mistake. }
5. dxe5 dxe5 6. Qd5
{ The weakness on  f7  can sometimes be exploited directly.  Here, Black's cramped development prevents him from defending this direct attack. }
6... Nh6 { Black defends  f7  ... } 7. Bxh6
{ ... so we remove the defender.  Black either loses a piece or gets mated. }
7... gxh6 8. Qxf7#
{ Usually,  f7  needs to be attacked via sacrificial means, but the direct attack can also work. }
