1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Bc5 5. c3 dxc3
{ This is a standard trap in the Scotch Gambit.  There are lots of open lines, and White can take advantage of the undefended Bishop on  c5  . }
6. Bxf7+
{ 6.Qd5  first is a good try, but Black's  6...Qe7  defends both  f7  (and the Bishop.) }
6... Kxf7 7. Qd5+ { This time it is the Queen that follows up with the check. }
7... Ke8 8. Qxc5
{ White was down a pawn to start, so he hasn't gained any material, but Black's King can't castle and will thus be a target for the rest of the game. }
