{ Buckle - NN, London 1840 } 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Bc4 Nc6 5. d3 Nge7
6. Bg5 Bg4 7. Nd5 Nd4
{ We can see many of the same elements as Legal, but it's not identical. In particular, the Nd5 blocks the Bishop from getting to  f7  . Nonetheless ... }
8. Nxe5 Bxd1
{ 8...dxe5  9.Qxg4  leaves Black only down a pawn, but if he goes for the greedy  Nxc2+ ?  10.Kd1  Nxa1  then  11.Bb5+  wins his Queen. This is a fun variation, where White's active pieces completely swarm Black's sleeping army. Time is everything. }
9. Nf6+
{ The Knight leaps out of the way of the Bishop with check.   9.Nc7+ ??  is a similar idea, but  Qxc7  10.Bxf7+  Kd8  isn't mate ! Oops. }
9... gxf6 10. Bxf7# *

