[Black "Tactical Section - The King's Diagonal 1"]
[Result "*"]

{ If  f7  is the weakest square on the board, then  h5-e8  is the weakest diagonal; from Black's perspective, it would be  f2  and  h4-e1  , respectively.  In this course, I refer to this weakness as the King's Diagonal.  Few pieces can easily interfere, and if it's open it can decide the game instantly, as in the famous Fool's Mate. }
1. g4 e5 2. f4 Qh4#
{ I know, I know.  'Smithy, no one will ever do this.'  True, but the THREAT of doing this, usually by sacrifice, is often decisive.  We will look at simple examples and then get to more impressive ones. }
