{ bayunaroto  (2032)  vs. chess_pizza1  (2393)    Source: @@LinkStart@@https://lichess.org/SN50T01L/@@LinkEnd@@  Game includes the lichess analysis. }
1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. Nxd4 Nf6 { B33 Sicilian Defense: Open } 5.
Nxc6 bxc6 6. Bd3
{ This is a relatively innocuous sideline ... but it beats a master in 11 moves, so you have to respect it.  As a general rule, if a move follows opening principles, and Bd3 is a normal developing move, then you should respect it, no matter what theory, computers or anyone else says. }
6... d5 7. e5 Nd7 8. e6
{ The Lichess computer analysis considers this a mistake, but it's a thematic attacking move that contains a large amount of poison.    -0.04 -0.58 Inaccuracy. Best move was  Qe2.  8.Qe2  g6  9.f4  f6  10.exf6  Nxf6  11.Nd2  Bg7  12.Nf3  O-O }
8... fxe6
{ Ever wanted to beat someone rated nearly 2400 in 11 moves?  Here's your chance! }
9. Qh5+ { Things are now primed for a standard King's Diagonal attack. } 9...
g6 10. Bxg6+
{ I'm slightly disappointed White did not sacrifice his Queen here. } 10...
hxg6 11. Qxg6#
{ And that's mate.  The most striking thing about this game?  Black was rated nearly 2400, and with a high rating of nearly 2500, and he lost to a simple King's Diagonal attack.  Opening Fundamentals work! }
