1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. Nc3 Nf6 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3
{ At first glance White has a small lead in development and good central control, but his Bishop is a potential weakness. }
7... Nxd4
{ Black moves his Knight and gets ready for his c-pawn to spring up the board. }
8. Nxd4 exd4 9. Qxd4 c5
{ This now comes with tempo against the Queen, and after she moves... } 10. Qe3
c4
{ ... the Bishop is caged.  Moving a Knight to allow the c-pawn to march is a very common idea, and here it came with tempo to trap the Bishop. }
