{ Ever wanted to beat Smithy?  Here's your chance!  This is taken from one of my own games.  I played Black, and it looks like I'm doing great: better development, more control of the center, safer King, what's not to like? }
1. c4
{ White's pawns can march with tempo, and suddenly my Bishop will find itself short on squares. }
1... Nde7 2. c5 Ba5 3. b4
{ And just like that my Bishop is trapped!  In the original position, the Bishop looked absolutely beautiful, but the Noah's Ark trap can spring very quickly when the pawns move with tempo.  Fun fact: my opponent  (rated 1900)  missed this idea in the game.  So did I  (rated 2050 at the time)  .  Even strong players miss these fundamentals on occasion.  This also means if you saw this, you're playing better than me.  Congrats! }
