1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
{ Amongst newer chess players, many miss the possibilities created by the Qa5+ in the opening.  This is a common double-attack motif in many positions.  Here is the purest example. }
5. e5
{ White confidently advances in the center, thinking he is gaining space and time and life is great. }
5... Qa5+
{ The Queen comes with check, allowing Black to pick up the free pawn. } 6. Nc3
Qxe5+
{ The Qa5+  (or Qa4+ from White's perspective)  allows the Queen to fork anything on the fifth rank.  There are numerous opening traps that make use of this possibility.  We'll look at several of them. }
