[SetUp "1"]

{ There is a type of tactic that is related to the Bxf7+ sacrifices we looked at earlier. Instead of mating the King, these grab the Queen. Here is the simplest example: }
1. Bxf7+
{ This forces the King away from the defence of the Queen.   1.Qxd8+  This is the obvious move, but much weaker  Kxd8  2.Bxf7  White doesn't even win a pawn because  Nxe4  wins it right back. }
1... Kxf7 2. Qxd8
{ It's very easy to get this tactic wrong. That is, the temptation is to exchange Queens and then win a pawn on  f7  . Instead, we invert the move order and win the Queen ! }
*

