[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Section II - Common Tactics"]
[Black "Tactical Section - The Pawn Fork Trick 2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Bc5
{ Let's look at a different reaction to the Pawn Fork Trick. } 4. Nxe5 Bxf2+
{ At first glance this looks smart, but ... } 5. Kxf2 Nxe5 6. d4
{ ... after d4, White gains time against the Knight and has complete control of the center.  Do you remember the Halloween Gambit game from the Principles Section?  The position is now similar, but White hasn't had to sacrifice a piece!  White has a massive advantage because of his center. }
