[White "Section II - Common Tactics"]
[Black "Tactical Section - The Pawn Fork Trick 3"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Bc4 O-O 6. O-O
{ Another example of the same trick. } 6... Nxe4 7. Nxe4 d5 8. Bd3 dxe4 9. Bxe4
{ Because of the Pawn Fork Trick, Black has exchanged a pair of pieces, relieving his space cramp, and he now has pressure on the d-pawn.  Nd7-f6 is another possible maneuver, gaining time against the  Be4  .  Black's position has become easier to play, if nothing else. }
