[Black "Game 11.1: Young Smithy - Tex, Internet 2004"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqk2r/2p2pp1/p1np1n1p/1pb1p3/4P3/1B3N1P/PPPP1PP1/RNBQR1K1 w kq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ From Young Smithy-Tex, Internet 2003, how should White continue? } 1. c3
{ We should seek to control the center.  c3 prepares d4 next move, which will also push Black back.    1.Nc3  is a normal move that is nonetheless a slight mistake: it develops a piece but doesn't fight for the center. At any point Black can play  Na5  to win the two Bishops, or he could try a strategy like  Rb8  and a6-a5-a4 to Noah's Ark our Bishop.  1.c3  fights for the center and also gives our Bishop room to escape. }
1... g5 { Black does a funky move.  Okay... } 2. d4
{ Seizing the center, as planned. } 2... exd4 3. cxd4 Bb4 4. Nc3
{ White has finished development, has complete control of the center and can now prepare a middlegame plan.  The opening has gone about as good as it can get. }
*

