[White "Section III - Annotated Games"]
[Black "Game 11.2: Young Smithy - Tex, Internet 2004"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bq1rk1/2p2p2/p2p1n1p/bp2P1p1/1n1P4/1BNQ1N1P/PP3PP1/R1B1R1K1 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White's Queen is attacked.  What should he do? } 1. Qg6+
{ A common idea against the castled King!  The  f7  -pawn is pinned, so the Queen invades right away. }
1... Kh8 2. Qxh6+
{ 2.Qxf6  wins a piece, which of course is good, but the continued attack is even stronger. }
2... Nh7 3. Bxg5
{ White finishes development while also winning material AND generating a winning attack.  Very nice indeed.  From Young Smithy-Tex, Internet 2004. }
