[SetUp "1"]

{ How should White continue development? } 1. Bd3
{ Developing the Bishop to its best diagonal.  Nf3 is also good.  Developing the Bc1 makes less sense because, with the open e-file, White should be focusing on castling as quickly as possible. }
1... Qe7+ 2. Ne2
{ 2.Be3  should likely be avoided, as after  2...Nf6  3.Nf3  Ng4  Black immediately targets the pinned piece and White is feeling the pressure.   2.Qe2  should also be avoided for structural reasons, as after  2...dxc4  3.Bxc4  Nf6  Black has a great version of the Isolated Queen Pawn position. This is beyond the scope of this course, so let's keep it simple: if Black puts his Queen on an open e-file, we should try to castle as fast as possible and get a Rook there. Hence, developing the Knight is best. }
2... Nf6 3. O-O
{ White has castled, and now he can use the open e-file against Black's King and/or Queen.  From Young Smithy - sompon, Internet 2004. }
