{ White's Bishop is attacked.  What should he do? } 1. Bg5
{ Develop with tempo!  The most powerful idea in the opening.  Retreating our Bishop would give Black a tempo to finish development.  Instead, we force him to defend.  Opening the e-file with Nxe5, which also protects the Bc4, was also possible but nowhere near as strong. }
1... f6
{ In the game Horvath-Mayer, Budapest 1917, Black played Ne7 instead.  What is the refutation to f6? }
2. dxe5
{ Again White doesn't retreat but rather opens the position up even more.  Black could take either piece, but he is helpless regardless against White's lead in development. }
2... fxg5
{ 2...Nxc4  allows  3.exf6+  with a discovered check by the Rook.  3...Kf8  4.fxg7+  Kxg7  5.Bxd8  and White won the Queen. }
3. exd6+
{ White completely opens the e-file and has a winning attack.  Black's forces are either not developed or are too far away from the King to help defend. }
