[SetUp "1"]

1... Nxg4
{ In Netzer - Mundet Riera, 2006 White has gambited a pawn on  g4  .  How should she continue development? }
2. Rg1
{ Logical: the Rook attacks the Knight on the newly open file and pressures the  g7  -pawn, making it harder for the  f8  -Bishop to develop. }
2... Ngf6 3. Bc4
{ Bringing the Bishop to its best square on an open diagonal, attacking  f7  . }
3... h6 4. Be3 { Developing the final piece to its only available square. }
4... c6 5. dxe5
{ White has a big lead in development, so she should try to open the position and create some open lines.  White has a nice initiative for the pawn and good attacking chances. }
