{ Congratulations!  You've completed the opening fundamentals!  Have some cake or pie or something and celebrate.  By coming this far, you have learned the fundamental opening principles, studied the most common opening tactics and reviewed over two dozen master-level games.  Your understanding of the opening is now on excellent foundation.  Now is the time to put these ideas into your own games.  Follow the opening principles, be aware of the tactical patterns and seek to punish common mistakes.  The more you use these ideas, they better you'll understand them, and inevitably, you'll find questions or positions that I didn't cover.  Feel free to ask me for input, and this course will evolve as more and more feedback comes in.  Conversely, if there were things I didn't cover, or that I didn't cover enough, or that you just didn't like, let me know and I'll see what I can do.  Thank you for using this course, and best of luck in your chess journey!  -- Jonathan 'SmithyQ' Pettit }
