{ The general principles are great and wonderful and will transform your game, but when you sit down at the board, you will face real problems posed by real people in real games. You will want and need specific advice more than general principles. That's where this section comes in.  This appendix gives concrete advice in certain common situations. These are NOT principles. They are practical guidelines. They tend to allow us to reach playable positions. You will not refute your opponent, but you won't lose in 8 moves either.  Note that this is just that, advice. You are not compelled to study or follow these recommendations. The computer will frequently say other moves are better. That's fine. This is practical advice, designed to be easy to use and hard to forget. }
